+# Pruned
+
+- Sort-key registry / dict mapping key -> sort lambda: rejected. Only ONE real
+  variant (`text`) is required now. argparse `choices=["text"]` plus a single
+  `if args.sort == "text"` is enough; a registry/strategy table is premature
+  abstraction until a second key (id/created) actually exists.
+- Adding a `sort()` helper to store.py: rejected. The seam is presentation in
+  cmd_list; store.py stays a pure source of truth, keeps the corridor to one file.
